# Drizzle ORM Database Rules

All database interactions must use Drizzle ORM. Never use raw SQL strings or other query builders.

## Schema

Tables are defined in [src/db/schema.ts](mdc:src/db/schema.ts):

- `decksTable` — stores flashcard decks (id, userId, title, description, createdAt, updatedAt)
- `cardsTable` — stores individual cards (id, deckId, front, back, createdAt, updatedAt)

Always import tables and relations from `@/db/schema`.

## Querying

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — use Drizzle query builder
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decksTable, cardsTable } from "@/db/schema";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";

const decks = await db.select().from(decksTable).where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));

// ❌ BAD — never use raw SQL
const decks = await db.execute(sql`SELECT * FROM decks WHERE user_id = ${userId}`);
```

## Mutations

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
await db.insert(decksTable).values({ userId, title, description });
await db.update(decksTable).set({ title }).where(eq(decksTable.id, id));
await db.delete(decksTable).where(eq(decksTable.id, id));
```

## Relations

Use Drizzle's `with` for joining related data:

```typescript
const deckWithCards = await db.query.decksTable.findFirst({
  where: eq(decksTable.id, deckId),
  with: { cards: true },
});
```
